Example
Use
var
to declare variables:
public class Main {
  public int test = 10;

public static void main(String[] args) {
    var x = 5;
    var main = new Main();
    System.out.println(x);
    System.out.println(main.test);
  }
}

Definition and Usage
The
var
keyword allows a variable to be initialized without having to declare its type. The type of the variable depends on the type of the data that is being assigned to it.
The
var
keyword was introduced in Java 10.
